model.amazon_selling_partner.stg_amazon_.name: stg_amazon_selling_partner__orders

amazon_order_id.name: amazon_order_id
amazon_order_id.description: An Amazon-defined order identifier, in 3-7-7 format.

automated_shipping_setting_automated_shi.name: automated_shipping_setting_automated_ship_method
automated_shipping_setting_automated_shi.description: Auto-generated ship method for SSA orders.

automated_shipping_setting_has_automated.name: automated_shipping_setting_has_automated_shipping_settings
automated_shipping_setting_has_automated.description: When true, this order has automated shipping settings generated by Amazon. This order could be identified as an SSA order.

buyer_info_purchase_order_number.name: buyer_info_purchase_order_number
buyer_info_purchase_order_number.description: The purchase order (PO) number entered by the buyer at checkout. Only returned for orders where the buyer entered a PO number at checkout.

earliest_delivery_date.name: earliest_delivery_date
earliest_delivery_date.description: The start of the time period within which you have committed to fulfill the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders.

earliest_ship_date.name: earliest_ship_date
earliest_ship_date.description: The start of the time period within which you have committed to ship the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders. Note: EarliestShipDate might not be returned for orders placed before February 1, 2013.

easy_ship_shipment_status.name: easy_ship_shipment_status
easy_ship_shipment_status.description: The status of the Amazon Easy Ship order. This property is only included for Amazon Easy Ship orders. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#easyshipshipmentstatus).

electronic_invoice_status.name: electronic_invoice_status
electronic_invoice_status.description: The status of the electronic invoice. Only available for Easy Ship orders and orders in the BR marketplace. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#electronicinvoicestatus).

fulfillment_channel.name: fulfillment_channel
fulfillment_channel.description: Whether the order was fulfilled by Amazon (AFN) or by the seller (MFN).

fulfillment_supply_source_id.name: fulfillment_supply_source_id
fulfillment_supply_source_id.description: The sourceId of the location from where you want the order fulfilled.

has_regulated_items.name: has_regulated_items
has_regulated_items.description: Whether the order contains regulated items which may require additional approval steps before being fulfilled.

is_access_point_order.name: is_access_point_order
is_access_point_order.description: When true, this order is marked to be delivered to an Access Point. The access location is chosen by the customer. Access Points include Amazon Hub Lockers, Amazon Hub Counters, and pickup points operated by carriers.

is_business_order.name: is_business_order
is_business_order.description: When true, the order is an Amazon Business order. An Amazon Business order is an order where the buyer is a Verified Business Buyer.

is_estimated_ship_date_set.name: is_estimated_ship_date_set
is_estimated_ship_date_set.description: When true, the estimated ship date is set for the order. Only returned for Sourcing on Demand orders.

is_global_express_enabled.name: is_global_express_enabled
is_global_express_enabled.description: When true, the order is a GlobalExpress order.

is_iba.name: is_iba
is_iba.description: When true, the item within this order was bought and re-sold by Amazon Business EU SARL (ABEU). By buying and instantly re-selling your items, ABEU becomes the seller of record, making your inventory available for sale to customers who would not otherwise purchase from a third-party seller.

is_ispu.name: is_ispu
is_ispu.description: When true, this order is marked to be picked up from a store rather than delivered.

is_premium_order.name: is_premium_order
is_premium_order.description: When true, the order has a Premium Shipping Service Level Agreement. For more information about Premium Shipping orders, refer to "Premium Shipping Options" in the Seller Central Help for your marketplace.

is_prime.name: is_prime
is_prime.description: When true, the order is a seller-fulfilled Amazon Prime order.

is_replacement_order.name: is_replacement_order
is_replacement_order.description: When true, this is a replacement order.

is_sold_by_ab.name: is_sold_by_ab
is_sold_by_ab.description: When true, the item within this order was bought and re-sold by Amazon Business EU SARL (ABEU). By buying and instantly re-selling your items, ABEU becomes the seller of record, making your inventory available for sale to customers who would not otherwise purchase from a third-party seller.

last_update_date.name: last_update_date
last_update_date.description: The date when the order was last updated. Note: LastUpdateDate is returned with an incorrect date for orders that were last updated before 2009-04-01.

latest_delivery_date.name: latest_delivery_date
latest_delivery_date.description: The end of the time period within which you have committed to fulfill the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders that do not have a PendingAvailability, Pending, or Canceled status.

latest_ship_date.name: latest_ship_date
latest_ship_date.description: The end of the time period within which you have committed to ship the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders. Note: LatestShipDate might not be returned for orders placed before February 1, 2013.

marketplace_id.name: marketplace_id
marketplace_id.description: The unobfuscated marketplace identifier. Different marketplace values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/marketplace-ids).

number_of_items_shipped.name: number_of_items_shipped
number_of_items_shipped.description: The number of items shipped for the order.

number_of_items_unshipped.name: number_of_items_unshipped
number_of_items_unshipped.description: The number of items unshipped for the order.

order_channel.name: order_channel
order_channel.description: The order channel for the first item in the order.

order_status.name: order_status
order_status.description: The current order status. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#orderstatus).

order_total_amount.name: order_total_amount
order_total_amount.description: The total charge for this order.

order_total_currency_code.name: order_total_currency_code
order_total_currency_code.description: The three-digit currency code in which the order total is measured. In ISO 4217 format.

order_type.name: order_type
order_type.description: The order's type. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#ordertype).

payment_method.name: payment_method
payment_method.description: The payment method for the order. This property is limited to COD and CVS payment methods. Unless you need the specific COD payment information provided by the PaymentExecutionDetailItem object, Amazon recommends using the PaymentMethodDetails table to get payment method information.

promise_response_due_date.name: promise_response_due_date
promise_response_due_date.description: Indicates the date by which the seller must respond to the buyer with an estimated ship date. Only returned for Sourcing on Demand orders.

purchase_date.name: purchase_date
purchase_date.description: The date when the order was created.

replaced_order_id.name: replaced_order_id
replaced_order_id.description: The order ID value for the order that is being replaced. Returned only if IsReplacementOrder = true.

sales_channel.name: sales_channel
sales_channel.description: The sales channel for the first item in the order.

seller_order_id.name: seller_order_id
seller_order_id.description: An order identifier that is specified by the seller. Used to select only the orders that match the order identifier. If SellerOrderId is specified, then FulfillmentChannels, OrderStatuses, PaymentMethod, LastUpdatedAfter, LastUpdatedBefore, and BuyerEmail cannot be specified.

shipment_service_level_category.name: shipment_service_level_category
shipment_service_level_category.description: The shipment service level category for the order. Possible values: Expedited, FreeEconomy, NextDay, Priority, SameDay, SecondDay, Scheduled, and Standard.

default_ship_from_location_address_line_.name: default_ship_from_location_address_line_1
default_ship_from_location_address_line_.description: Street address of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_address_line_.name: default_ship_from_location_address_line_2
default_ship_from_location_address_line_.description: Additional street address information of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_address_line_.name: default_ship_from_location_address_line_3
default_ship_from_location_address_line_.description: Additional street address information of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_address_type.name: default_ship_from_location_address_type
default_ship_from_location_address_type.description: Address type of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_city.name: default_ship_from_location_city
default_ship_from_location_city.description: City of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_country_code.name: default_ship_from_location_country_code
default_ship_from_location_country_code.description: Country code (two-character country code, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 format.) of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_county.name: default_ship_from_location_county
default_ship_from_location_county.description: County of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_district.name: default_ship_from_location_district
default_ship_from_location_district.description: District of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_municipality.name: default_ship_from_location_municipality
default_ship_from_location_municipality.description: Municipality of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_name.name: default_ship_from_location_name
default_ship_from_location_name.description: Name of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_phone.name: default_ship_from_location_phone
default_ship_from_location_phone.description:
Associated phone number of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

Note: In some cases, the buyer phone number is suppressed:
a. Phone is suppressed for all AFN (fulfilled by Amazon) orders.
b. Phone is suppressed for the shipped MFN (fulfilled by seller) order when the current date is past the Latest Delivery Date.

default_ship_from_location_postal_code.name: default_ship_from_location_postal_code
default_ship_from_location_postal_code.description: Postal code of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_state_or_regi.name: default_ship_from_location_state_or_region
default_ship_from_location_state_or_regi.description: State or region of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

with item_summary as (
    select *
    from {{ ref('stg_amazon_selling_partner__item_summary') }}
),

item_product_type as (

    select *
    from {{ ref('stg_amazon_selling_partner__item_product_type') }} 
),

item_image as (

    select *
    from {{ ref('stg_amazon_selling_partner__item_image') }}
),

item_images as (

    select 
        source_relation,
        asin,
        marketplace_id,
        count(*) as count_images,
        sum(case when variant = 'SWATCH' then 1 else 0 end) as count_swatch_images

    from item_image 
    group by 1,2,3
),

item_display_group_sales_rank as (

    select *
    from {{ ref('stg_amazon_selling_partner__item_display_group_sales_rank') }} 
),

item_classification_sales_rank as (

    select *
    from {{ ref('stg_amazon_selling_partner__item_classification_sales_rank') }} 
),

item_relationship as (

    select *
    from {{ ref('stg_amazon_selling_partner__item_relationship') }} 
),

parent_variation_relationship as (

    select *
    from item_relationship
    where type = 'VARIATION'
),

package_hierarchy_relationship as (

    select *
    from item_relationship
    where type = 'PACKAGE_HIERARCHY'
),

item_dimension as (

    select *
    from {{ ref('stg_amazon_selling_partner__item_dimension') }} 
),

item_identifier as (

    select *
    from {{ ref('stg_amazon_selling_partner__item_identifier') }} 
),

item_identifiers as (

    select 
        asin,
        source_relation,
        marketplace_id
        {# iterate over identifier types (from https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/catalog-items-api-v2022-04-01-reference#identifierstype) that aren't already logged elsewhere (ASIN) #}
        {% for identifier_type in ['SKU', 'EAN', 'GTIN', 'ISBN', 'JAN', 'MINSAN', 'UPC'] %}
            , cast(max(case when identifier_type = '{{ identifier_type }}' then identifier end) as {{ dbt.type_string() }}) as {{ identifier_type | lower }}
        {% endfor %}
    from item_identifier
    group by 1,2,3
),

joined as (

    select 
        item_summary.source_relation,
        item_summary.marketplace_id,
        item_summary.asin,
        item_summary.item_name,
        item_summary.display_name,
        item_summary.brand,
        item_summary.color,
        item_summary.size,
        item_summary.style,
        item_summary.package_quantity,
        item_summary.manufacturer,
        item_summary.contributors,
        item_product_type.product_type,
        item_summary.item_classification,
        item_summary.classification_id,
        item_classification_sales_rank.link as classification_sales_rank_link,
        item_classification_sales_rank.rank as classification_sales_rank,
        item_summary.website_display_group,
        item_summary.website_display_group_name,
        item_display_group_sales_rank.link as website_display_group_sales_rank_link,
        item_display_group_sales_rank.rank as website_display_group_sales_rank,
        item_summary.release_date,
        item_summary.is_memorabilia,
        item_summary.is_adult_product,
        item_summary.is_autographed,
        item_summary.is_trade_in_eligible,

        item_summary.model_number,
        item_summary.part_number,
        parent_variation_relationship.parent_asin as parent_variation_asin,
        package_hierarchy_relationship.parent_asin as parent_package_container_asin,
        item_identifiers.sku,
        item_identifiers.ean,
        item_identifiers.gtin, 
        item_identifiers.isbn, 
        item_identifiers.jan,
        item_identifiers.minsan, 
        item_identifiers.upc,
        
        item_images.count_images,
        item_images.count_swatch_images,
        item_dimension.item_height_unit,
        item_dimension.item_height_value,
        item_dimension.item_length_unit,
        item_dimension.item_length_value,
        item_dimension.item_weight_unit,
        item_dimension.item_weight_value,
        item_dimension.item_width_unit,
        item_dimension.item_width_value,
        item_dimension.package_height_unit,
        item_dimension.package_height_value,
        item_dimension.package_length_unit,
        item_dimension.package_length_value,
        item_dimension.package_weight_unit,
        item_dimension.package_weight_value,
        item_dimension.package_width_unit,
        item_dimension.package_width_value

    from item_summary
    left join item_product_type
        on item_summary.asin = item_product_type.asin 
        and item_summary.marketplace_id = item_product_type.marketplace_id
        and item_summary.source_relation = item_product_type.source_relation
    left join item_images
        on item_summary.asin = item_images.asin 
        and item_summary.marketplace_id = item_images.marketplace_id
        and item_summary.source_relation = item_images.source_relation
    left join item_display_group_sales_rank
        on item_summary.asin = item_display_group_sales_rank.asin 
        and item_summary.website_display_group = item_display_group_sales_rank.website_display_group
        and item_summary.source_relation = item_display_group_sales_rank.source_relation
    left join item_classification_sales_rank
        on item_summary.asin = item_classification_sales_rank.asin 
        and item_summary.classification_id = item_classification_sales_rank.classification_id
        and item_summary.source_relation = item_classification_sales_rank.source_relation
    left join parent_variation_relationship
        on item_summary.asin = parent_variation_relationship.child_asin
        and item_summary.source_relation = parent_variation_relationship.source_relation
    left join package_hierarchy_relationship
        on item_summary.asin = package_hierarchy_relationship.child_asin
        and item_summary.source_relation = package_hierarchy_relationship.source_relation
    left join item_identifiers
        on item_summary.asin = item_identifiers.asin 
        and item_summary.marketplace_id = item_identifiers.marketplace_id
        and item_summary.source_relation = item_identifiers.source_relation
    left join item_dimension 
        on item_summary.asin = item_dimension.asin 
        and item_summary.marketplace_id = item_dimension.marketplace_id
        and item_summary.source_relation = item_dimension.source_relation
)

source.amazon_selling_partner.amazon_sel.name: orders

amazon_order_id.name: amazon_order_id
amazon_order_id.description: An Amazon-defined order identifier, in 3-7-7 format.

automated_shipping_setting_automated_shi.name: automated_shipping_setting_automated_ship_method
automated_shipping_setting_automated_shi.description: Auto-generated ship method for SSA orders.

automated_shipping_setting_has_automated.name: automated_shipping_setting_has_automated_shipping_settings
automated_shipping_setting_has_automated.description: When true, this order has automated shipping settings generated by Amazon. This order could be identified as an SSA order.

buyer_info_buyer_email.name: buyer_info_buyer_email
buyer_info_buyer_email.description: The anonymized email address of the buyer.

buyer_info_buyer_county.name: buyer_info_buyer_county
buyer_info_buyer_county.description: The county of the buyer. This attribute is only available in the Brazil marketplace.

buyer_info_buyer_name.name: buyer_info_buyer_name
buyer_info_buyer_name.description: The buyer name or the recipient name.

buyer_info_purchase_order_number.name: buyer_info_purchase_order_number
buyer_info_purchase_order_number.description: The purchase order (PO) number entered by the buyer at checkout. Only returned for orders where the buyer entered a PO number at checkout.

buyer_invoice_preference.name: buyer_invoice_preference
buyer_invoice_preference.description: The buyer's invoicing preference. Sellers can use this data to issue electronic invoices for orders in Turkey. Possible values = `INDIVIDUAL` or `BUSINESS`

buyer_tax_info_buyer_business_address.name: buyer_tax_info_buyer_business_address
buyer_tax_info_buyer_business_address.description: Business buyer's address.Only available in the TR marketplace.

buyer_tax_info_buyer_legal_company_name.name: buyer_tax_info_buyer_legal_company_name
buyer_tax_info_buyer_legal_company_name.description: Business buyer's company legal name.	Only available in the TR marketplace.

buyer_tax_info_buyer_tax_office.name: buyer_tax_info_buyer_tax_office
buyer_tax_info_buyer_tax_office.description: Business buyer's company tax office.	Only available in the TR marketplace.

buyer_tax_info_buyer_tax_registration_id.name: buyer_tax_info_buyer_tax_registration_id
buyer_tax_info_buyer_tax_registration_id.description: Business buyer's tax registration ID.	Only available in the TR marketplace.

cba_displayable_shipping_label.name: cba_displayable_shipping_label
cba_displayable_shipping_label.description: Custom ship label for Checkout by Amazon (CBA).

earliest_delivery_date.name: earliest_delivery_date
earliest_delivery_date.description: The start of the time period within which you have committed to fulfill the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders.

earliest_ship_date.name: earliest_ship_date
earliest_ship_date.description: The start of the time period within which you have committed to ship the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders. Note: EarliestShipDate might not be returned for orders placed before February 1, 2013.

easy_ship_shipment_status.name: easy_ship_shipment_status
easy_ship_shipment_status.description: The status of the Amazon Easy Ship order. This property is only included for Amazon Easy Ship orders. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#easyshipshipmentstatus).

electronic_invoice_status.name: electronic_invoice_status
electronic_invoice_status.description: The status of the electronic invoice. Only available for Easy Ship orders and orders in the BR marketplace. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#electronicinvoicestatus).

fulfillment_channel.name: fulfillment_channel
fulfillment_channel.description: Whether the order was fulfilled by Amazon (AFN) or by the seller (MFN).

fulfillment_supply_source_id.name: fulfillment_supply_source_id
fulfillment_supply_source_id.description: The sourceId of the location from where you want the order fulfilled.

has_regulated_items.name: has_regulated_items
has_regulated_items.description: Whether the order contains regulated items which may require additional approval steps before being fulfilled.

is_access_point_order.name: is_access_point_order
is_access_point_order.description: When true, this order is marked to be delivered to an Access Point. The access location is chosen by the customer. Access Points include Amazon Hub Lockers, Amazon Hub Counters, and pickup points operated by carriers.

is_business_order.name: is_business_order
is_business_order.description: When true, the order is an Amazon Business order. An Amazon Business order is an order where the buyer is a Verified Business Buyer.

is_estimated_ship_date_set.name: is_estimated_ship_date_set
is_estimated_ship_date_set.description: When true, the estimated ship date is set for the order. Only returned for Sourcing on Demand orders.

is_global_express_enabled.name: is_global_express_enabled
is_global_express_enabled.description: When true, the order is a GlobalExpress order.

is_iba.name: is_iba
is_iba.description: When true, the item within this order was bought and re-sold by Amazon Business EU SARL (ABEU). By buying and instantly re-selling your items, ABEU becomes the seller of record, making your inventory available for sale to customers who would not otherwise purchase from a third-party seller.

is_ispu.name: is_ispu
is_ispu.description: When true, this order is marked to be picked up from a store rather than delivered.

is_premium_order.name: is_premium_order
is_premium_order.description: When true, the order has a Premium Shipping Service Level Agreement. For more information about Premium Shipping orders, refer to "Premium Shipping Options" in the Seller Central Help for your marketplace.

is_prime.name: is_prime
is_prime.description: When true, the order is a seller-fulfilled Amazon Prime order.

is_replacement_order.name: is_replacement_order
is_replacement_order.description: When true, this is a replacement order.

is_sold_by_ab.name: is_sold_by_ab
is_sold_by_ab.description: When true, the item within this order was bought and re-sold by Amazon Business EU SARL (ABEU). By buying and instantly re-selling your items, ABEU becomes the seller of record, making your inventory available for sale to customers who would not otherwise purchase from a third-party seller.

last_update_date.name: last_update_date
last_update_date.description: The date when the order was last updated. Note: LastUpdateDate is returned with an incorrect date for orders that were last updated before 2009-04-01.

latest_delivery_date.name: latest_delivery_date
latest_delivery_date.description: The end of the time period within which you have committed to fulfill the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders that do not have a PendingAvailability, Pending, or Canceled status.

latest_ship_date.name: latest_ship_date
latest_ship_date.description: The end of the time period within which you have committed to ship the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders. Note: LatestShipDate might not be returned for orders placed before February 1, 2013.

marketplace_id.name: marketplace_id
marketplace_id.description: The unobfuscated marketplace identifier. Different marketplace values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/marketplace-ids).

number_of_items_shipped.name: number_of_items_shipped
number_of_items_shipped.description: The number of items shipped for the order.

number_of_items_unshipped.name: number_of_items_unshipped
number_of_items_unshipped.description: The number of items unshipped for the order.

order_channel.name: order_channel
order_channel.description: The order channel for the first item in the order.

order_status.name: order_status
order_status.description: The current order status. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#orderstatus).

order_total_amount.name: order_total_amount
order_total_amount.description: The total charge for this order.

order_total_currency_code.name: order_total_currency_code
order_total_currency_code.description: The three-digit currency code in which the order total is measured. In ISO 4217 format.

order_type.name: order_type
order_type.description: The order's type. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#ordertype).

payment_method.name: payment_method
payment_method.description: The payment method for the order. This property is limited to COD and CVS payment methods. Unless you need the specific COD payment information provided by the PaymentExecutionDetailItem object, Amazon recommends using the PaymentMethodDetails table to get payment method information.

promise_response_due_date.name: promise_response_due_date
promise_response_due_date.description: Indicates the date by which the seller must respond to the buyer with an estimated ship date. Only returned for Sourcing on Demand orders.

purchase_date.name: purchase_date
purchase_date.description: The date when the order was created.

replaced_order_id.name: replaced_order_id
replaced_order_id.description: The order ID value for the order that is being replaced. Returned only if IsReplacementOrder = true.

sales_channel.name: sales_channel
sales_channel.description: The sales channel for the first item in the order.

seller_display_name.name: seller_display_name
seller_display_name.description: The seller’s friendly name registered in the marketplace where the sale took place. Sellers can use this data to issue electronic invoices for orders in Brazil. Note: This attribute is only available in the Brazil marketplace for the orders with Pending or Unshipped status.

seller_order_id.name: seller_order_id
seller_order_id.description: An order identifier that is specified by the seller. Used to select only the orders that match the order identifier. If SellerOrderId is specified, then FulfillmentChannels, OrderStatuses, PaymentMethod, LastUpdatedAfter, LastUpdatedBefore, and BuyerEmail cannot be specified.

shipment_service_level_category.name: shipment_service_level_category
shipment_service_level_category.description: The shipment service level category for the order. Possible values: Expedited, FreeEconomy, NextDay, Priority, SameDay, SecondDay, Scheduled, and Standard.

default_ship_from_location_address_line_.name: default_ship_from_location_address_line_1
default_ship_from_location_address_line_.description: Street address of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

default_ship_from_location_address_line_.name: default_ship_from_location_address_line_2

source.amazon_selling_partner.amazon_sel.name: order_item

order_item_id.name: order_item_id
order_item_id.description: An Amazon-defined item identifier for the associated item.

amazon_order_id.name: amazon_order_id
amazon_order_id.description: An Amazon-defined order identifier, in 3-7-7 format.

is_gift.name: is_gift
is_gift.description: Boolean that indicates whether the item is a gift.

is_transparency.name: is_transparency
is_transparency.description:
When true, the ASIN is enrolled in Transparency. The Transparency serial number that you must submit is determined by:

- 1D or 2D Barcode: This has a T logo. Submit either the 29-character alpha-numeric identifier beginning with AZ or ZA, or the 38-character Serialized Global Trade Item Number (SGTIN).
- 2D Barcode SN: Submit the 7- to 20-character serial number barcode, which likely has the prefix SN. The serial number is applied to the same side of the packaging as the GTIN (UPC/EAN/ISBN) barcode.
- QR code SN: Submit the URL that the QR code generates.

asin.name: asin
asin.description: The item's Amazon Standard Identification Number (ASIN).

buyer_requested_cancel_is_buyer_requeste.name: buyer_requested_cancel_is_buyer_requested_cancel
buyer_requested_cancel_is_buyer_requeste.description: Boolean indicating whether the buyer has requested cancellation.

buyer_requested_cancel_buyer_cancel_reas.name: buyer_requested_cancel_buyer_cancel_reason
buyer_requested_cancel_buyer_cancel_reas.description: The reason that the buyer requested cancellation.

condition_id.name: condition_id
condition_id.description: The condition of the item. Possible values: New, Used, Collectible, Refurbished, Preorder, and Club.

condition_note.name: condition_note
condition_note.description: The condition of the item, as described by the seller.

condition_subtype_id.name: condition_subtype_id
condition_subtype_id.description:
The subcondition of the item.

Possible values: New, Mint, Very Good, Good, Acceptable, Poor, Club, OEM, Warranty, Refurbished Warranty, Refurbished, Open Box, Any, and Other.

deemed_reseller_category.name: deemed_reseller_category
deemed_reseller_category.description:
The category of deemed reseller. This applies to selling partners that are not based in the EU and is used to help them meet the VAT Deemed Reseller tax laws in the EU and UK. 
Either `IOSS` (Import one stop shop. The item being purchased is not held in the EU for shipment) or `UOSS` (Union one stop shop. The item being purchased is held in the EU for shipment).

ioss_number.name: ioss_number
ioss_number.description: The IOSS number of the marketplace. Sellers shipping to the EU from outside the EU must provide this IOSS number to their carrier when Amazon has collected the VAT on the sale.

item_price_amount.name: item_price_amount
item_price_amount.description: The selling price of the order item. Note that an order item is an item and a quantity. This means that the value of ItemPrice is equal to the selling price of the item multiplied by the quantity ordered. ItemPrice excludes ShippingPrice and GiftWrapPrice.

item_price_currency_code.name: item_price_currency_code
item_price_currency_code.description: The three-digit currency code that the `item_price_amount` is listed in. In ISO 4217 format.

item_tax_amount.name: item_tax_amount
item_tax_amount.description: The tax on the item price.

item_tax_currency_code.name: item_tax_currency_code
item_tax_currency_code.description: The three-digit currency code that the `item_tax_amount` is listed in. In ISO 4217 format.

points_granted_monetary_amount.name: points_granted_monetary_amount
points_granted_monetary_amount.description: The monetary value of the Amazon Points granted.

points_granted_monetary_currency_code.name: points_granted_monetary_currency_code
points_granted_monetary_currency_code.description: The three-digit currency code that the `points_granted_monetary_amount` is listed in. In ISO 4217 format.

points_granted_points_number.name: points_granted_points_number
points_granted_points_number.description: The number of Amazon Points granted with the purchase of an item.

price_designation.name: price_designation
price_designation.description: Indicates that the selling price is a special price that is only available for Amazon Business orders. For more information about the Amazon Business Seller Program, refer to the Amazon Business [website](https://business.amazon.com/?ref_=b2b_mcs_L0_mlpr). Possible value(s): BusinessPrice

product_info_detail_number_of_items.name: product_info_detail_number_of_items
product_info_detail_number_of_items.description: The total number of items that are included in the ASIN.

promotion_discount_amount.name: promotion_discount_amount
promotion_discount_amount.description: The total of all promotional discounts in the offer.

promotion_discount_currency_code.name: promotion_discount_currency_code
promotion_discount_currency_code.description: The three-digit currency code that the `promotion_discount_amount` is listed in. In ISO 4217 format.

promotion_discount_tax_currency_code.name: promotion_discount_tax_currency_code
promotion_discount_tax_currency_code.description: The three-digit currency code that the `promotion_discount_tax_amount` is listed in. In ISO 4217 format.

promotion_discount_tax_amount.name: promotion_discount_tax_amount
promotion_discount_tax_amount.description: The tax on the total of all promotional discounts in the offer.

quantity_ordered.name: quantity_ordered
quantity_ordered.description: The number of items in the order.

scheduled_delivery_end_date.name: scheduled_delivery_end_date
scheduled_delivery_end_date.description: The end date of the scheduled delivery window in the time zone for the order destination. In ISO 8601 date time format.

scheduled_delivery_start_date.name: scheduled_delivery_start_date
scheduled_delivery_start_date.description: The start date of the scheduled delivery window in the time zone for the order destination. In ISO 8601 date time format.

seller_sku.name: seller_sku
seller_sku.description: The item's seller stock keeping unit (SKU).

serial_number_required.name: serial_number_required
serial_number_required.description: When true, the product type for this item has a serial number. Only returned for Amazon Easy Ship orders.

shipping_discount_amount.name: shipping_discount_amount
shipping_discount_amount.description: The discount on the shipping price.

shipping_discount_tax_currency_code.name: shipping_discount_tax_currency_code

shipping_price_currency_code.name: shipping_price_currency_code

shipping_tax_amount.name: shipping_tax_amount

store_chain_store_id.description: The store chain store identifier. Linked to a specific store in a store chain.

tax_collection_model.name: tax_collection_model
tax_collection_model.description: The tax collection model applied to the item. Possible value(s) can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#model).

macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__list_relati.name: postgres__list_relations_without_caching
macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__list_relati.macro_sql:
{% macro postgres__list_relations_without_caching(schema_relation) %}
  {% call statement('list_relations_without_caching', fetch_result=True) -%}
    select
      '{{ schema_relation.database }}' as database,
      tablename as name,
      schemaname as schema,
      'table' as type
    from pg_tables
    where schemaname ilike '{{ schema_relation.schema }}'
    union all
    select
      '{{ schema_relation.database }}' as database,
      viewname as name,
      schemaname as schema,
      'view' as type
    from pg_views
    where schemaname ilike '{{ schema_relation.schema }}'
    union all
    select
      '{{ schema_relation.database }}' as database,
      matviewname as name,
      schemaname as schema,
      'materialized_view' as type
    from pg_matviews
    where schemaname ilike '{{ schema_relation.schema }}'
  {% endcall %}
  {{ return(load_result('list_relations_without_caching').table) }}
{% endmacro %}

macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_show_in.name: postgres__get_show_indexes_sql
macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_show_in.macro_sql:
{% macro postgres__get_show_indexes_sql(relation) %}
    select
        i.relname                                   as name,
        m.amname                                    as method,
        ix.indisunique                              as "unique",
        array_to_string(array_agg(a.attname), ',')  as column_names
    from pg_index ix
    join pg_class i
        on i.oid = ix.indexrelid
    join pg_am m
        on m.oid=i.relam
    join pg_class t
        on t.oid = ix.indrelid
    join pg_namespace n
        on n.oid = t.relnamespace
    join pg_attribute a
        on a.attrelid = t.oid
        and a.attnum = ANY(ix.indkey)
    where t.relname = '{{ relation.identifier }}'
      and n.nspname = '{{ relation.schema }}'
      and t.relkind in ('r', 'm')
    group by 1, 2, 3
    order by 1, 2, 3
{% endmacro %}

macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_relatio.name: postgres__get_relations
macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_relatio.macro_sql:
{% macro postgres__get_relations() -%}

  {#
      -- in pg_depend, objid is the dependent, refobjid is the referenced object
      --  > a pg_depend entry indicates that the referenced object cannot be
      --  > dropped without also dropping the dependent object.
  #}

  {%- call statement('relations', fetch_result=True) -%}
    select distinct
        dependent_namespace.nspname as dependent_schema,
        dependent_class.relname as dependent_name,
        referenced_namespace.nspname as referenced_schema,
        referenced_class.relname as referenced_name

    -- Query for views: views are entries in pg_class with an entry in pg_rewrite, but we avoid
    -- a seq scan on pg_rewrite by leveraging the fact there is an "internal" row in pg_depend for
    -- the view...
    from pg_class as dependent_class
    join pg_namespace as dependent_namespace on dependent_namespace.oid = dependent_class.relnamespace
    join pg_depend as dependent_depend on dependent_depend.refobjid = dependent_class.oid
        and dependent_depend.classid = 'pg_rewrite'::regclass
        and dependent_depend.refclassid = 'pg_class'::regclass
        and dependent_depend.deptype = 'i'

    -- ... and via pg_depend (that has a row per column, hence the need for "distinct" above, and
    -- making sure to exclude the internal row to avoid a view appearing to depend on itself)...
    join pg_depend as joining_depend on joining_depend.objid = dependent_depend.objid
        and joining_depend.classid = 'pg_rewrite'::regclass
        and joining_depend.refclassid = 'pg_class'::regclass
        and joining_depend.refobjid != dependent_depend.refobjid

    -- ... we can find the tables they query from in pg_class, but excluding system tables. Note we
    -- don't need need to exclude _dependent_ system tables, because they only query from other
    -- system tables, and so are automatically excluded by excluding _referenced_ system tables
    join pg_class as referenced_class on referenced_class.oid = joining_depend.refobjid
    join pg_namespace as referenced_namespace on referenced_namespace.oid = referenced_class.relnamespace
        and referenced_namespace.nspname != 'information_schema'
        and referenced_namespace.nspname not like 'pg\_%'

    order by
        dependent_schema, dependent_name, referenced_schema, referenced_name;

  {%- endcall -%}

  {{ return(load_result('relations').table) }}
{% endmacro %}

doc.dbt.__overview__.name: __overview__
doc.dbt.__overview__.block_contents:
### Welcome!

Welcome to the auto-generated documentation for your dbt project!

### Navigation

You can use the `Project` and `Database` navigation tabs on the left side of the window to explore the models
in your project.

#### Project Tab
The `Project` tab mirrors the directory structure of your dbt project. In this tab, you can see all of the
models defined in your dbt project, as well as models imported from dbt packages.

#### Database Tab
The `Database` tab also exposes your models, but in a format that looks more like a database explorer. This view
shows relations (tables and views) grouped into database schemas. Note that ephemeral models are _not_ shown
in this interface, as they do not exist in the database.

### Graph Exploration
You can click the blue icon on the bottom-right corner of the page to view the lineage graph of your models.

On model pages, you'll see the immediate parents and children of the model you're exploring. By clicking the `Expand`
button at the top-right of this lineage pane, you'll be able to see all of the models that are used to build,
or are built from, the model you're exploring.

Once expanded, you'll be able to use the `--select` and `--exclude` model selection syntax to filter the
models in the graph. For more information on model selection, check out the [dbt docs](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/model-selection-syntax).

Note that you can also right-click on models to interactively filter and explore the graph.

---

### More information

- [What is dbt](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/introduction)?
- Read the [dbt viewpoint](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/viewpoint)
- [Installation](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/installation)
- Join the [dbt Community](https://www.getdbt.com/community/) for questions and discussion

doc.amazon_selling_partner.amazon_order_.name: amazon_order_id
doc.amazon_selling_partner.amazon_order_.block_contents: An Amazon-defined order identifier, in 3-7-7 format.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.automated_shi.name: automated_shipping_setting_automated_ship_method
doc.amazon_selling_partner.automated_shi.block_contents: Auto-generated ship method for SSA orders.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.automated_shi.name: automated_shipping_setting_has_automated_shipping_settings
doc.amazon_selling_partner.automated_shi.block_contents: When true, this order has automated shipping settings generated by Amazon. This order could be identified as an SSA order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_info_bu.name: buyer_info_buyer_county
doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_info_bu.block_contents: The county of the buyer. This attribute is only available in the Brazil marketplace.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_info_bu.name: buyer_info_buyer_email
doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_info_bu.block_contents: The anonymized email address of the buyer.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_info_bu.name: buyer_info_buyer_name
doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_info_bu.block_contents: The buyer name or the recipient name.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_info_pu.name: buyer_info_purchase_order_number
doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_info_pu.block_contents: The purchase order (PO) number entered by the buyer at checkout. Only returned for orders where the buyer entered a PO number at checkout.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_invoice.name: buyer_invoice_preference
doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_invoice.block_contents: The buyer's invoicing preference. Sellers can use this data to issue electronic invoices for orders in Turkey. Possible values = `INDIVIDUAL` or `BUSINESS`

doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_tax_inf.name: buyer_tax_info_buyer_business_address
doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_tax_inf.block_contents: Business buyer's address.Only available in the TR marketplace.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_tax_inf.name: buyer_tax_info_buyer_legal_company_name
doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_tax_inf.block_contents: Business buyer's company legal name.	Only available in the TR marketplace.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_tax_inf.name: buyer_tax_info_buyer_tax_office
doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_tax_inf.block_contents: Business buyer's company tax office.	Only available in the TR marketplace.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_tax_inf.name: buyer_tax_info_buyer_tax_registration_id
doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_tax_inf.block_contents: Business buyer's tax registration ID.	Only available in the TR marketplace.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.cba_displayab.name: cba_displayable_shipping_label
doc.amazon_selling_partner.cba_displayab.block_contents: Custom ship label for Checkout by Amazon (CBA).

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_address_line_1
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: Street address of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_address_line_2
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: Additional street address information of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_address_line_3
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: Additional street address information of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_address_type
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: Address type of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_city
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: City of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_country_code
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: Country code (two-character country code, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 format.) of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_county
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: County of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_district
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: District of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_municipality
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: Municipality of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_name
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: Name of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_phone
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents:
Associated phone number of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

Note: In some cases, the buyer phone number is suppressed:
a. Phone is suppressed for all AFN (fulfilled by Amazon) orders.
b. Phone is suppressed for the shipped MFN (fulfilled by seller) order when the current date is past the Latest Delivery Date.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_postal_code
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: Postal code of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.name: default_ship_from_location_state_or_region
doc.amazon_selling_partner.default_ship_.block_contents: State or region of the recommended location for the seller to ship the items from. It is calculated at checkout. The seller may or may not choose to ship from this location.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.earliest_deli.name: earliest_delivery_date
doc.amazon_selling_partner.earliest_deli.block_contents: The start of the time period within which you have committed to fulfill the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.earliest_ship.name: earliest_ship_date
doc.amazon_selling_partner.earliest_ship.block_contents: The start of the time period within which you have committed to ship the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders. Note: EarliestShipDate might not be returned for orders placed before February 1, 2013.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.easy_ship_shi.name: easy_ship_shipment_status
doc.amazon_selling_partner.easy_ship_shi.block_contents: The status of the Amazon Easy Ship order. This property is only included for Amazon Easy Ship orders. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#easyshipshipmentstatus).

doc.amazon_selling_partner.electronic_in.name: electronic_invoice_status
doc.amazon_selling_partner.electronic_in.block_contents: The status of the electronic invoice. Only available for Easy Ship orders and orders in the BR marketplace. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#electronicinvoicestatus).

doc.amazon_selling_partner.fulfillment_c.name: fulfillment_channel
doc.amazon_selling_partner.fulfillment_c.block_contents: Whether the order was fulfilled by Amazon (AFN) or by the seller (MFN).

doc.amazon_selling_partner.fulfillment_s.name: fulfillment_supply_source_id
doc.amazon_selling_partner.fulfillment_s.block_contents: The sourceId of the location from where you want the order fulfilled.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.has_regulated.name: has_regulated_items
doc.amazon_selling_partner.has_regulated.block_contents: Whether the order contains regulated items which may require additional approval steps before being fulfilled.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_access_poi.name: is_access_point_order
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_access_poi.block_contents: When true, this order is marked to be delivered to an Access Point. The access location is chosen by the customer. Access Points include Amazon Hub Lockers, Amazon Hub Counters, and pickup points operated by carriers.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_business_o.name: is_business_order
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_business_o.block_contents: When true, the order is an Amazon Business order. An Amazon Business order is an order where the buyer is a Verified Business Buyer.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_estimated_.name: is_estimated_ship_date_set
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_estimated_.block_contents: When true, the estimated ship date is set for the order. Only returned for Sourcing on Demand orders.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_global_exp.name: is_global_express_enabled
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_global_exp.block_contents: When true, the order is a GlobalExpress order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_iba.name: is_iba
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_iba.block_contents: When true, the item within this order was bought and re-sold by Amazon Business EU SARL (ABEU). By buying and instantly re-selling your items, ABEU becomes the seller of record, making your inventory available for sale to customers who would not otherwise purchase from a third-party seller.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_ispu.name: is_ispu
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_ispu.block_contents: When true, this order is marked to be picked up from a store rather than delivered.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_premium_or.name: is_premium_order
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_premium_or.block_contents: When true, the order has a Premium Shipping Service Level Agreement. For more information about Premium Shipping orders, refer to "Premium Shipping Options" in the Seller Central Help for your marketplace.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_prime.name: is_prime
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_prime.block_contents: When true, the order is a seller-fulfilled Amazon Prime order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_replacemen.name: is_replacement_order
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_replacemen.block_contents: When true, this is a replacement order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_sold_by_ab.name: is_sold_by_ab
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_sold_by_ab.block_contents: When true, the item within this order was bought and re-sold by Amazon Business EU SARL (ABEU). By buying and instantly re-selling your items, ABEU becomes the seller of record, making your inventory available for sale to customers who would not otherwise purchase from a third-party seller.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.last_update_d.name: last_update_date
doc.amazon_selling_partner.last_update_d.block_contents: The date when the order was last updated. Note: LastUpdateDate is returned with an incorrect date for orders that were last updated before 2009-04-01.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.latest_delive.name: latest_delivery_date
doc.amazon_selling_partner.latest_delive.block_contents: The end of the time period within which you have committed to fulfill the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders that do not have a PendingAvailability, Pending, or Canceled status.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.latest_ship_d.name: latest_ship_date
doc.amazon_selling_partner.latest_ship_d.block_contents: The end of the time period within which you have committed to ship the order. In ISO 8601 date time format. Only returned for seller-fulfilled orders. Note: LatestShipDate might not be returned for orders placed before February 1, 2013.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.marketplace_i.name: marketplace_id
doc.amazon_selling_partner.marketplace_i.block_contents: The unobfuscated marketplace identifier. Different marketplace values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/marketplace-ids).

doc.amazon_selling_partner.number_of_ite.name: number_of_items_shipped
doc.amazon_selling_partner.number_of_ite.block_contents: The number of items shipped for the order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.number_of_ite.name: number_of_items_unshipped
doc.amazon_selling_partner.number_of_ite.block_contents: The number of items unshipped for the order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_channel.name: order_channel
doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_channel.block_contents: The order channel for the first item in the order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_status.name: order_status
doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_status.block_contents: The current order status. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#orderstatus).

doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_total_a.name: order_total_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_total_a.block_contents: The total charge for this order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_total_c.name: order_total_currency_code
doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_total_c.block_contents: The three-digit currency code in which the order total is measured. In ISO 4217 format.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_type.name: order_type
doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_type.block_contents: The order's type. Possible values can be found [here](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/orders-api-v0-reference#ordertype).

doc.amazon_selling_partner.payment_metho.name: payment_method
doc.amazon_selling_partner.payment_metho.block_contents: The payment method for the order. This property is limited to COD and CVS payment methods. Unless you need the specific COD payment information provided by the PaymentExecutionDetailItem object, Amazon recommends using the PaymentMethodDetails table to get payment method information.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.promise_respo.name: promise_response_due_date
doc.amazon_selling_partner.promise_respo.block_contents: Indicates the date by which the seller must respond to the buyer with an estimated ship date. Only returned for Sourcing on Demand orders.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.purchase_date.name: purchase_date
doc.amazon_selling_partner.purchase_date.block_contents: The date when the order was created.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.replaced_orde.name: replaced_order_id
doc.amazon_selling_partner.replaced_orde.block_contents: The order ID value for the order that is being replaced. Returned only if IsReplacementOrder = true.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.sales_channel.name: sales_channel
doc.amazon_selling_partner.sales_channel.block_contents: The sales channel for the first item in the order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.seller_displa.name: seller_display_name
doc.amazon_selling_partner.seller_displa.block_contents: The seller’s friendly name registered in the marketplace where the sale took place. Sellers can use this data to issue electronic invoices for orders in Brazil. Note: This attribute is only available in the Brazil marketplace for the orders with Pending or Unshipped status.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.seller_order_.name: seller_order_id
doc.amazon_selling_partner.seller_order_.block_contents: An order identifier that is specified by the seller. Used to select only the orders that match the order identifier. If SellerOrderId is specified, then FulfillmentChannels, OrderStatuses, PaymentMethod, LastUpdatedAfter, LastUpdatedBefore, and BuyerEmail cannot be specified.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipment_serv.name: shipment_service_level_category
doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipment_serv.block_contents: The shipment service level category for the order. Possible values: Expedited, FreeEconomy, NextDay, Priority, SameDay, SecondDay, Scheduled, and Standard.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.name: shipping_address_address_line_1
doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.block_contents:
Street address of the shipping address for the order.

Note:
1. ShippingAddress is only available for orders with the following status values: Unshipped, PartiallyShipped, Shipped and InvoiceUnconfirmed.
2. The ShippingAddress contains restricted data. Use the Restricted Data Token (RDT) and restricted SPDS roles to access the restricted data in ShippingAddress. For example, Name, AddressLine1, AddressLine2, AddressLine3, Phone, AddressType, and ExtendedFields.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.name: shipping_address_country_code
doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.block_contents:
Country code (two-character country code, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 format) of the shipping address for the order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.name: shipping_address_district
doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.block_contents:
District of the shipping address for the order.

1. ShippingAddress is only available for orders with the following status values: Unshipped, PartiallyShipped, Shipped and InvoiceUnconfirmed.
2. The ShippingAddress contains restricted data. Use the Restricted Data Token (RDT) and restricted SPDS roles to access the restricted data in ShippingAddress. For example, Name, AddressLine1, AddressLine2, AddressLine3, Phone, AddressType, and ExtendedFields.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.name: shipping_address_municipality
doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.block_contents:
Municipality of the shipping address for the order.

1. ShippingAddress is only available for orders with the following status values: Unshipped, PartiallyShipped, Shipped and InvoiceUnconfirmed.
2. The ShippingAddress contains restricted data. Use the Restricted Data Token (RDT) and restricted SPDS roles to access the restricted data in ShippingAddress. For example, Name, AddressLine1, AddressLine2, AddressLine3, Phone, AddressType, and ExtendedFields.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.name: shipping_address_name
doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.block_contents:
Name of the shipping address for the order.

Note:
1. ShippingAddress is only available for orders with the following status values: Unshipped, PartiallyShipped, Shipped and InvoiceUnconfirmed.
2. The ShippingAddress contains restricted data. Use the Restricted Data Token (RDT) and restricted SPDS roles to access the restricted data in ShippingAddress. For example, Name, AddressLine1, AddressLine2, AddressLine3, Phone, AddressType, and ExtendedFields.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.name: shipping_address_phone
doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.block_contents:
Phone number of the shipping address for the order.

Note:
1. ShippingAddress is only available for orders with the following status values: Unshipped, PartiallyShipped, Shipped and InvoiceUnconfirmed.
2. The ShippingAddress contains restricted data. Use the Restricted Data Token (RDT) and restricted SPDS roles to access the restricted data in ShippingAddress. For example, Name, AddressLine1, AddressLine2, AddressLine3, Phone, AddressType, and ExtendedFields.
3. In some cases, the buyer phone number is suppressed:
  a. Phone is suppressed for all AFN (fulfilled by Amazon) orders.
  b. Phone is suppressed for the shipped MFN (fulfilled by seller) order when the current date is past the Latest Delivery Date.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.name: shipping_address_postal_code
doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.block_contents:
Postal code of the shipping address for the order.

2. The ShippingAddress contains restricted data. Use the Restricted Data Token (RDT) and restricted SPDS roles to access the restricted data in ShippingAddress. For example, Name, AddressLine1, AddressLine2, AddressLine3, Phone, AddressType, and ExtendedFields.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_addr.block_contents:

doc.amazon_selling_partner.asin.name: asin
doc.amazon_selling_partner.asin.block_contents: The item's Amazon Standard Identification Number (ASIN).

doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_request.name: buyer_requested_cancel_buyer_cancel_reason
doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_request.block_contents: The reason that the buyer requested cancellation.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_request.name: buyer_requested_cancel_is_buyer_requested_cancel
doc.amazon_selling_partner.buyer_request.block_contents: Boolean indicating whether the buyer has requested cancellation.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.condition_id.name: condition_id
doc.amazon_selling_partner.condition_id.block_contents: The condition of the item. Possible values: New, Used, Collectible, Refurbished, Preorder, and Club.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.condition_not.name: condition_note
doc.amazon_selling_partner.condition_not.block_contents: The condition of the item, as described by the seller.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.condition_sub.name: condition_subtype_id
doc.amazon_selling_partner.condition_sub.block_contents:
The subcondition of the item.

Possible values: New, Mint, Very Good, Good, Acceptable, Poor, Club, OEM, Warranty, Refurbished Warranty, Refurbished, Open Box, Any, and Other.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.deemed_resell.name: deemed_reseller_category
doc.amazon_selling_partner.deemed_resell.block_contents:
The category of deemed reseller. This applies to selling partners that are not based in the EU and is used to help them meet the VAT Deemed Reseller tax laws in the EU and UK. 
Either `IOSS` (Import one stop shop. The item being purchased is not held in the EU for shipment) or `UOSS` (Union one stop shop. The item being purchased is held in the EU for shipment).

doc.amazon_selling_partner.ioss_number.name: ioss_number
doc.amazon_selling_partner.ioss_number.block_contents: The IOSS number of the marketplace. Sellers shipping to the EU from outside the EU must provide this IOSS number to their carrier when Amazon has collected the VAT on the sale.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_gift.name: is_gift
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_gift.block_contents: Boolean that indicates whether the item is a gift.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_transparen.name: is_transparency
doc.amazon_selling_partner.is_transparen.block_contents:
When true, the ASIN is enrolled in Transparency. The Transparency serial number that you must submit is determined by:

- 1D or 2D Barcode: This has a T logo. Submit either the 29-character alpha-numeric identifier beginning with AZ or ZA, or the 38-character Serialized Global Trade Item Number (SGTIN).
- 2D Barcode SN: Submit the 7- to 20-character serial number barcode, which likely has the prefix SN. The serial number is applied to the same side of the packaging as the GTIN (UPC/EAN/ISBN) barcode.
- QR code SN: Submit the URL that the QR code generates.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_item_pr.name: total_item_price_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_item_pr.block_contents: The total selling price of the order's line items. Note that an individual order item is an item and a quantity. This means that the value of ItemPrice is equal to the selling price of the item multiplied by the quantity ordered. ItemPrice excludes ShippingPrice and GiftWrapPrice.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.item_price_am.name: item_price_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.item_price_am.block_contents: The selling price of the order item. Note that an order item is an item and a quantity. This means that the value of ItemPrice is equal to the selling price of the item multiplied by the quantity ordered. ItemPrice excludes ShippingPrice and GiftWrapPrice.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.item_price_cu.name: item_price_currency_code
doc.amazon_selling_partner.item_price_cu.block_contents: The three-digit currency code that the `item_price_amount` is listed in. In ISO 4217 format.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.item_tax_amou.name: item_tax_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.item_tax_amou.block_contents: The tax on the item price.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_item_ta.name: total_item_tax_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_item_ta.block_contents: The total tax on the order items' price.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.item_tax_curr.name: item_tax_currency_code
doc.amazon_selling_partner.item_tax_curr.block_contents: The three-digit currency code that the `item_tax_amount` is listed in. In ISO 4217 format.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_item_id.name: order_item_id
doc.amazon_selling_partner.order_item_id.block_contents: An Amazon-defined item identifier for the associated item.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.points_grante.name: points_granted_monetary_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.points_grante.block_contents: The monetary value of the Amazon Points granted.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.points_grante.name: points_granted_monetary_currency_code
doc.amazon_selling_partner.points_grante.block_contents: The three-digit currency code that the `points_granted_monetary_amount` is listed in. In ISO 4217 format.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.points_grante.name: points_granted_points_number
doc.amazon_selling_partner.points_grante.block_contents: The number of Amazon Points granted with the purchase of an item.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.price_designa.name: price_designation
doc.amazon_selling_partner.price_designa.block_contents: Indicates that the selling price is a special price that is only available for Amazon Business orders. For more information about the Amazon Business Seller Program, refer to the Amazon Business [website](https://business.amazon.com/?ref_=b2b_mcs_L0_mlpr). Possible value(s): BusinessPrice

doc.amazon_selling_partner.product_info_.name: product_info_detail_number_of_items
doc.amazon_selling_partner.product_info_.block_contents: The total number of items that are included in the ASIN.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.promotion_dis.name: promotion_discount_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.promotion_dis.block_contents: The total of all promotional discounts in the offer.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_promoti.name: total_promotion_discount_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_promoti.block_contents: The total of all promotional discounts in the offers associated with the order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.promotion_dis.name: promotion_discount_currency_code
doc.amazon_selling_partner.promotion_dis.block_contents: The three-digit currency code that the `promotion_discount_amount` is listed in. In ISO 4217 format.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.promotion_dis.name: promotion_discount_tax_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.promotion_dis.block_contents: The tax on the total of all promotional discounts in the offer.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_promoti.name: total_promotion_discount_tax_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_promoti.block_contents: The total tax on all promotional discounts in the offers associated with the order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.promotion_dis.name: promotion_discount_tax_currency_code
doc.amazon_selling_partner.promotion_dis.block_contents: The three-digit currency code that the `promotion_discount_tax_amount` is listed in. In ISO 4217 format.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.quantity_orde.name: quantity_ordered
doc.amazon_selling_partner.quantity_orde.block_contents: The number of items in the order.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.scheduled_del.name: scheduled_delivery_end_date
doc.amazon_selling_partner.scheduled_del.block_contents: The end date of the scheduled delivery window in the time zone for the order destination. In ISO 8601 date time format.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.scheduled_del.name: scheduled_delivery_start_date
doc.amazon_selling_partner.scheduled_del.block_contents: The start date of the scheduled delivery window in the time zone for the order destination. In ISO 8601 date time format.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.seller_sku.name: seller_sku
doc.amazon_selling_partner.seller_sku.block_contents: The item's seller stock keeping unit (SKU).

doc.amazon_selling_partner.serial_number.name: serial_number_required
doc.amazon_selling_partner.serial_number.block_contents: When true, the product type for this item has a serial number. Only returned for Amazon Easy Ship orders.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_disc.name: shipping_discount_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_disc.block_contents: The discount on the shipping price.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_shippin.name: total_shipping_discount_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_shippin.block_contents: The total discount on the order's shipping prices.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_disc.name: shipping_discount_currency_code
doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_disc.block_contents: The three-digit currency code that the `shipping_discount_amount` is listed in. In ISO 4217 format.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_disc.name: shipping_discount_tax_amount

doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_shippin.name: total_shipping_discount_tax_amount

doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_shippin.name: total_shipping_tax_amount
doc.amazon_selling_partner.total_shippin.block_contents: The total tax on the order's shipping price.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.shipping_tax_.name: shipping_tax_currency_code

doc.amazon_selling_partner.item_summary.name: item_summary
doc.amazon_selling_partner.item_summary.block_contents: Summary details of an Amazon catalog item for the indicated Amazon marketplace.

doc.amazon_selling_partner._fivetran_syn.name: _fivetran_synced
doc.amazon_selling_partner._fivetran_syn.block_contents: UTC timestamp of when the row was last successfully synced.

doc.amazon_selling_partner._fivetran_del.name: _fivetran_deleted
doc.amazon_selling_partner._fivetran_del.block_contents: Boolean indicating whether the item relationship was deleted. Filtered out of the staging model.

doc.amazon_selling_partner.adult_product.name: adult_product

doc.amazon_selling_partner.autographed.name: autographed
doc.amazon_selling_partner.autographed.block_contents: Identifies an Amazon catalog item is autographed by a player or celebrity.

test.amazon_selling_partner_integration_.name: consistency_orders
test.amazon_selling_partner_integration_.raw_code:
{{ config(
    tags="fivetran_validations",
    enabled=var('fivetran_validation_tests_enabled', false)
) }}

with prod as (
    select
        {{ dbt_utils.star(from=ref('amazon_selling_partner__orders'), except=var('consistency_test_exclude_fields', '[]')) }}
    from {{ target.schema }}_amazon_selling_partner_prod.amazon_selling_partner__orders
),

dev as (
    select
        {{ dbt_utils.star(from=ref('amazon_selling_partner__orders'), except=var('consistency_test_exclude_fields', '[]')) }}
    from {{ target.schema }}_amazon_selling_partner_dev.amazon_selling_partner__orders
),

prod_not_in_dev as (
    -- rows from prod not found in dev
    select * from prod
    except distinct
    select * from dev
),

dev_not_in_prod as (
    -- rows from dev not found in prod
    select * from dev
    except distinct
    select * from prod
),

final as (
    select
        *,
        'from prod' as source
    from prod_not_in_dev

    union all -- union since we only care if rows are produced

    select
        *,
        'from dev' as source
    from dev_not_in_prod
)

select *
from final
